[1] Cholera - Uganda (Bulambuli District)
Date: Thu 4 Feb 2016
Source: AllAfrica, The Monitor [edited
http://allafrica.com/stories/201602040813.html


A cholera outbreak has been declared in Bulambuli District [eastern Uganda] after the district health department registered 4 suspected cases. The District Health Officer, Dr Muhammadi Mulongo, said the 1st suspected case was reported in Muyembe Sub-county. "Let me take this opportunity to inform the local community that there is a cholera outbreak in our district. And so far, 4 cases have been detected from Muyembe sub-county," said Dr Mulongo.

The district health office has set up one treatment centre at Muyembe Health centre IV. He said they have notified the health ministry and the WHO about the outbreak. "We have set up a team of health officers to sensitize the local community on hygiene and sanitation," he said. Dr Mulongo said they have not registered any death.

[Byline: Yahudu Kitunzi]

