******
[2] Cholera - Kenya (Menu & Tharaka Nithi Counties)
Date: Fri 5 Feb 2016
Source: The Star [edited]
http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/2016/02/05/cholera-shuts-food-shops-in-meru-tharaka_c1289112


All food businesses in Gatithini, Mukothima, and Kithima in Meru and Tharaka Nithi counties have been ordered shut because of a cholera outbreak. 2 people have died in 2 weeks and at least 35 hospitalized. 12 people have been admitted to hospital in Gatithini, 12 in Marimanti, 6 in Mukothima, and 5 in Kathangacini.

Kenya Red Cross Society Mt Kenya region manager Gitonga Mugambi yesterday [4 Feb 2016] said it is educating residents about good hygiene. 100 cholera cases have been reported so far, he said. "All food outlets and hotels have been closed and we are encouraging people to eat from home," Mugambi said. "We have distributed chlorine and aqua tablets for water treatment." He said the situation is not improving.

A clinical officer, 2 nurses, 2 public health officers, and 4 health workers have been deployed to affected areas. Mugambi said there are conflicting reports on the number of cholera cases in Meru county. County health executive William Muraa says 10 cholera cases have been reported and one resident has been treated and discharged. The others are undergoing treatment, he says.

[Byline: Kirimil Murithi]

